bilingual.source: The stigma of being unemployed can be hard to overcome.
bilingual.target: 失业的耻辱可能很难克服。

bilingual.source: Many unemployed people are looking for new opportunities.
bilingual.target: 许多失业的人正在寻找新的机会。

bilingual.source: Overcoming the stigmas of being unemployed can be challenging.
bilingual.target: 克服失业的耻辱可能是一个挑战。

bilingual.source: Ask anyone newly unemployed what they want and the answer is always: a job.
bilingual.target: 问任何刚失业的人他们想要什么，答案总是：一份工作。

bilingual.source: Unemployed young men are more likely to live with their parents than the employed.
bilingual.target: 失业的年轻人比有工作的人更有可能和父母住在一起。

bilingual.source: The unemployed usually lead a hard life.
bilingual.target: 失业的人生活一般很困难。

bilingual.source: There are more unemployed than ever before.
bilingual.target: 现在失业的人比以往任何时候都多。

bilingual.source: When unemployed, I went to drive a pedicab.
bilingual.target: 我失业的时候就去蹬三轮车.
1938年，内布拉斯加州失业的原铁路工人。

yingyinNormal.en: But I'm unemployed, my music is all I really have now. Well music, and making my own shoes. Pretty?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是我失业了，我只剩下音乐，音乐，还有自己做鞋子，很美吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, right, the unemployed piano player who gave his trust fund to charity? I'm splitting the muffin with him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是喔，那个把信托基金全捐给慈善机构的失业钢琴师吗？我要回去跟他分那个松饼的。

yingyinNormal.en: Its goal is simple: to put the ten million Americans who are unemployed to work. All of them. If you want a job, you get one.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其目的很简单，让一千万没有工作的美国人有工作，每一个想工作的人都会有工作。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。
